#: ../../source/gentle_gis_introduction/AGentleIntroductionToGIS.rst:51
# 9af779d8dd9d4e2284c4c3570eddcd41
msgid "GIS is becoming an increasingly important tool in environmental management, retail, military, police, tourism and many other spheres of our daily lives. If you use a computer or a cell phone, you have probably already used a GIS in some form without even realising it. Maybe it was a map on a web site, Google Earth, an information booth or your cell phone telling you where you are. Proprietary GIS software (software that cannot be freely shared or modified) is available that will let you do everything we describe in these worksheets and a lot more. However this software is usually very expensive or otherwise limits your freedom to copy, share and modify the software. GIS vendors sometimes make an exception for educational activities, providing cheaper or free copies of their software. They do this knowing that if teachers and learners get to know their software, they will be reluctant to learn other packages. When learners leave school they will go into the workplace and buy the commercial software, never knowing that there are free alternatives that they could be using."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/gentle_gis_introduction/AGentleIntroductionToGIS.rst:61
# fac894e4daa84f3eaa7e877fe9ce3fc4
msgid "With Quantum GIS, we offer an alternative - software that is free of cost and free in a social sense. You can make as many copies as you like. When learners leave school one day they can use this software to build their skills, solve problems at work and make the world a better place."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/gentle_gis_introduction/AGentleIntroductionToGIS.rst:66
# e0726aa31bc3447f9f875d2a944112b7
msgid "When you buy commercial software, you limit your options for the future. By learning, using and sharing Free and Open Source Software, you are building your own skills, freeing money to be spent on important things like food and shelter and boosting our own economy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/gentle_gis_introduction/AGentleIntroductionToGIS.rst:70
# ddfe4224a47c471281864d9f74eb4f06
msgid "By sponsoring the creation of this resource, the DLA has created a foundation to which young minds can be exposed. Exciting possibilities lie ahead when principles of free sharing of knowledge and data are embraced. For this we give our heartfelt thanks to the DLA!"
msgstr ""

