#: ../../source/gentle_gis_introduction/AGentleIntroductionToGIS.rst:144
# 8c1514659cdf405894cb292b50e3ab4f
msgid "What is GIS Software / a GIS Application?:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/gentle_gis_introduction/AGentleIntroductionToGIS.rst:146
# 6f3a744fcf804ea6bcd09d43a795796c
msgid "You can see an example of what a **GIS Application** looks like in Illustration  . GIS Applications are normally programs with a graphical user interface that can be manipulated using the mouse and keyboard. The application provides **menus** near to the top of the window (File, Edit etc.) which, when clicked using the mouse, show a panel of **actions**. These actions provide a way for you to tell the GIS Application what you want to do. For example you may use the menus to tell the GIS Application to add a new layer to the display output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/gentle_gis_introduction/AGentleIntroductionToGIS.rst:155
# e92b02f39fd147c8938adf095f6ec656
msgid "**Toolbars** (rows of small pictures that can be clicked with the mouse) normally sit just below the menus and provide a quicker way to use frequently needed actions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/gentle_gis_introduction/AGentleIntroductionToGIS.rst:161
# 10aa529d072b4c318f345493ce7fce0e
msgid "A common function of GIS Applications is to display **map layers**. Map layers are stored as files on a disk or as records in a database. Normally each map layer will represent something in the real world – a roads layer for example will have data about the street network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/gentle_gis_introduction/AGentleIntroductionToGIS.rst:166
# bd8bd23112674f4eaa13f82713872a42
msgid "When you open a layer in the GIS Application it will appear in the **map view**. The map view shows a graphic representing your layer. When you add more than one layer to a map view, the layers are overlaid on top of each other. Illustrations  to   show a map view that has several layers being added to it. An important function of the map view is to allow you to zoom in to magnify, zoom out to see a greater area and move around (panning) in the map."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/gentle_gis_introduction/AGentleIntroductionToGIS.rst:184
# c7ba51f889294b6f9202d535824bda71
msgid "Another common feature of GIS Applications is the **map legend**. The map legend provides a list of layers that have been loaded in the GIS Application. Unlike a paper map legend, the map legend or 'layers list' in the GIS Application provides a way to re-order, hide, show and group layers. Changing the layer order is done by clicking on a layer in the legend, holding the mouse button down and then dragging the layer to a new position. In Illustrations  and  , the map legend is shown as the area to the left of the GIS Application window. By changing the layer order, the way that layers are drawn can be adjusted – in this case so that rivers are drawn over the roads instead of below them."
msgstr ""

